reviews.review: There were some really cheesy scenes, but overall, as a Star Wars fan for 40 plus years it was a satisfying end to the saga.
Probably my favorite of Episodes 7, 8 and 9.  And definitely better than 1, 2, and 3.  Way better.
Lived up to the hype but tried too hard to check all the PC boxes and not “offend” anyone.

Bringing back Palpatine negated the prequels and original trilogy. Kylo Ren and the special effects were great however despite a very weak concluding story to a trilogy of trilogies. Disney, do better.

J. J. Abrams spends a good amount of this film righting the wrongs of Rian Johnson. Covering up the many disliked plot points of "The Last Jedi", "The Rise of Skywalker" almost feels like a new start with Abrams opening up many doors for a bigger universe behind the film's plot. New, likable characters, a great amount of fan service that feels like the director knows a bit about Star Wars' universe and a convoluted but conclusive story that gives the impression, Abrams felt forced to put two films into one. It's only sad to see what could have been, hadn't it been for Johnson's defilement of the sequel saga...
Contrary to what the critics said, The Rise of the Skywalker is an outstanding movie with a gran finale for this amazing saga. A must see.

Better than Force Awakens and definitely far better than The Last Jedi. Not the best conclusion and the addition of The Emperor should have happened in the last movie but several moments are very exciting and nostalgic. Felt like a Star Wars Legends Comic. Should be a 5 but pointless plot McGuffins hold it back

I was expecting a really bad movie after The Last Jedi, but this actually wasn't bad.  The bad parts in this movie are actually from having to clean up tLJ issues.  Would have been much better if you made this into two movies.

Starts out slow, but once the directors stop worrying about homage to the old characters, the pace picks up and the movie finds its pacing and storytelling. Daisy Ridley and Adam Driver carry the movie and the movie is best when the two of them share the screen.
As usual, the critics are wrong. This last story is brilliantly Star Wars! A perfect ending!
